</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-30_ pf-text-1"><strong>Direct pressure</strong> -The first and most effective step in controlling bleeding.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-32_ pf-text-1"><strong>Tourniquet </strong>- A device that applies pressure to a limb or extremity to stop severe bleeding.




</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-34_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-35_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-36_ pf-heading-1-h3">Legislation and regulations</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-38_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In the UK, the Health and Safety (First-Aid) Regulations 1981 mandate that employers provide adequate and appropriate equipment, facilities, and personnel to ensure immediate and effective first aid in the event of an injury. This includes training employees in handling emergency situations involving significant blood loss.
